@page "/about"

<h1>About Nexus Code Intelligence Platform</h1>

<div class="card">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>Nexus Code Intelligence Platform is a Roslyn-based code analysis system for C# and Unity projects.</p>
    <p>It provides deep semantic understanding of code through Knowledge Graphs, Symbol Search, and MCP integration for AI agents.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
    <table class="table">
        <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Technology</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>Framework</td><td>.NET 10, C#</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Analysis</td><td>Roslyn (Microsoft.CodeAnalysis)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Storage</td><td>SQLite, In-Memory Graph</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Vector DB</td><td>Qdrant, InMemory</td></tr>
            <tr><td>AI</td><td>Ollama (nomic-embed-text, mxbai-embed-large, bge-m3)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Frontend</td><td>Blazor</td></tr>
            <tr><td>API</td><td>ASP.NET Core REST</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Protocol</td><td>MCP (Model Context Protocol)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>Features</h2>
    <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
        <li class="feature-item">Roslyn-based semantic analysis</li>
        <li class="feature-item">Knowledge Graph with 15+ edge types</li>
        <li class="feature-item">Symbol search with fuzzy matching</li>
        <li class="feature-item">Call graph analysis (callers/callees)</li>
        <li class="feature-item">Interface implementation tracking</li>
        <li class="feature-item">Unity-specific intelligence (MonoBehaviour, SerializeField)</li>
        <li class="feature-item">MCP Server with 10 tools for AI agents</li>
        <li class="feature-item">Graph RAG for context generation</li>
        <li class="feature-item">Multi-repository support</li>
        <li class="feature-item">Repository health analysis</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <pre>Code → Roslyn Analysis → Knowledge Graph → Symbol Search → MCP → Embeddings → Graph RAG</pre>
</div>

